[Désolé pour les réceptions multiples]

Chers collègues,

J'ai le plaisir d'annoncer la parution d'un livre, co-écrit par Patrick 
Bosc et moi-même, sur les requêtes à préférences modélisées dans le 
cadre de la théorie des ensembles flous (avec un avant-propos de Ronald 
R. Yager).

Fuzzy Preference Queries to Relational Databases
Olivier Pivert and Patrick Bosc
Imperial College Press, 2012
ISBN: 978-1-84816-869-5 (http://www.worldscibooks.com/compsci/p840.html)

The manipulation of databases is an integral part of a world which is 
becoming increasingly and pervasively information-focused. This book 
puts forward a suggestion to advocate preference queries and fuzzy sets 
as a central concern in database queries and offers an important 
contribution to the design of intelligent information systems. It 
provides a comprehensive study on fuzzy preference queries in the 
context of relational databases. Preference queries, a recent hot topic 
in database research, provide a basis for rank-ordering the items 
retrieved, which is especially valuable for large sets of answers.

This book aims to show that fuzzy set theory constitutes a highly 
expressive framework for modeling preference queries. It presents a 
study of the algorithmic aspects related to the evaluation of such 
queries in order to demonstrate that this framework offers a good 
trade-off between expressivity and efficiency. Numerous examples and 
proofs are liberally and lucidly demonstrated throughout, and greatly 
enhance the detailed theoretical aspects explored in the book.

Researchers working in databases will greatly benefit from this 
comprehensive and up-to-date study of fuzzy preference queries, and it 
will also become an invaluable reference point for postgraduate students 
interested in advanced database techniques.

-- 
Olivier Pivert
Professeur des Universités
Responsable de l'equipe de recherche Irisa/Pilgrim
Irisa-Enssat
